main event: Multiple Air Force navigators observed an unidentified orange-white object with erratic movements over Houston, Texas on May 20, 1952.
interesting points: The object was first spotted at a 45-degree elevation, moved to a 180-degree bearing, and made a turn.
The object exhibited erratic side-to-side movements while maintaining a straight course.
The sighting lasted for approximately 90 seconds.
The Air Force navigators were conducting practice when they noticed the object.
The weather was clear at the time of the sighting.
